{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/regel/loudml/issues/42","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/regel/loudml","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/regel/loudml/issues/42/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/regel/loudml/issues/42/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/regel/loudml/issues/42/events","html_url":"https://github.com/regel/loudml/issues/42","id":362232280,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWUzNjIyMzIyODA=","number":42,"title":"LoudML 1.4 doesn't use the measurement field when used with ES","user":{"login":"jorgelbg","id":1291846,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyOTE4NDY=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1291846?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgelbg","html_url":"https://github.com/jorgelbg","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgelbg/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgelbg/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgelbg/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgelbg/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgelbg/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgelbg/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgelbg/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgelbg/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgelbg/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":5,"created_at":"2018-09-20T15:06:05Z","updated_at":"2018-11-05T15:03:23Z","closed_at":"2018-10-25T07:38:29Z","author_association":"NONE","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"In our case, we've several ES indexes with a `_type` set to `logs`. \r\n\r\nSetting the measurement to `logs` in the model definition, it doesn't have any impact on the request sent to ES:\r\n\r\nIn the model definition:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    \"bucket_interval\": \"5m\",\r\n    \"default_datasource\": \"elastic\",\r\n    \"timestamp_field\": \"@timestamp\",\r\n    \"features\": [\r\n      {\r\n        \"default\": 0,\r\n        \"metric\": \"max\",\r\n        \"field\": \"error_count\",\r\n        \"measurement\": \"logs\",\r\n        \"name\": \"count_errors\",\r\n        \"anomaly_type\": \"low_high\",\r\n        \"match_all\": [\r\n          {\"tag\": \"partner_id\", \"value\": \"1234\"}\r\n        ]\r\n      }\r\n    ],\r\n```\r\n\r\nInspecting the traffic with tcpdump on port 9200:\r\n\r\n```\r\nGET /errorratio*/doc/_search?size=0 HTTP/1.1\r\nHost: 10.1.3.100:9200\r\nAccept-Encoding: identity\r\nContent-Length: 443\r\ncontent-type: application/json\r\nconnection: keep-alive\r\n....\r\n```\r\n\r\nAlthough multiple document types in the same index are deprecated it is still possible to have only one that is not `doc`.","closed_by":{"login":"regel","id":355557,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM1NTU1Nw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/355557?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/regel","html_url":"https://github.com/regel","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/regel/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/regel/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/regel/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/regel/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/regel/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/regel/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/regel/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/regel/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/regel/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/regel/loudml/issues/42/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/regel/loudml/issues/42/time